# Pulse_Brain — example credentials (copy to .env in your instance; never commit .env).
# Everything here is OPTIONAL. The brain runs with none of it: the embedding adapter
# defaults to local (no key, on-device), and there is no required cloud credential.
# Set a value only for the capability you opt into. Secrets follow the global credential
# map (.env / ~/.env) — referenced by name, never hardcoded in any file.

# Embedding API adapter (S17) — only if you choose the API embedding adapter over the
# local default. The local adapter needs NO key.
# PULSE_EMBEDDING_API_KEY=

# Watchlist / feed credentials (S11 monitor) — only if a source you watch needs auth.
# Add one line per source, named for the source.
# EXAMPLE_FEED_TOKEN=
